  "summary": "Telegram/Firebase exfiltration via hijacked console on import",
  "details": "The package's main entry (index.js) replaces the global console with a Proxy that forwards every log argument to a hardcoded Telegram Bot API endpoint and a Firebase URL. Static YARA rules independently confirm Telegram exfiltration patterns in index.js and src/6cc.js (a static pattern match). The legitimate-looking fetch wrapper in src/index.js is shadowed by the malicious main field, demonstrating intent to deceive. Hardcoded bot token, multiple chat_ids, and import-time execution constitute unambiguous credential/log theft — no benign use case exists for silently shipping console contents to a Telegram bot.",
